theorem Topology.interior_inter_eq_inter_interior_of_isOpen_right
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} (hB : IsOpen B) :
    interior (A ∩ B) = interior A ∩ B := by
  -- We prove mutual inclusion.
  apply Set.Subset.antisymm
  · -- `⊆` direction
    intro x hx
    -- `x ∈ interior A` by monotonicity of `interior`.
    have hx_intA : x ∈ interior A :=
      (interior_mono (by
        intro y hy
        exact hy.1)) hx
    -- `x ∈ B` since `interior (A ∩ B) ⊆ A ∩ B`.
    have hx_B : x ∈ B := by
      have : x ∈ (A ∩ B : Set X) := interior_subset hx
      exact this.2
    exact And.intro hx_intA hx_B
  · -- `⊇` direction
    intro x hx
    rcases hx with ⟨hx_intA, hxB⟩
    -- The open neighbourhood `interior A ∩ B` exhibits that `x` is in the interior.
    have h_open : IsOpen (interior A ∩ B) :=
      isOpen_interior.inter hB
    have h_subset : (interior A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A ∩ B := by
      intro y hy
      exact And.intro (interior_subset hy.1) hy.2
    have : x ∈ interior (A ∩ B) :=
      (mem_interior.2 ⟨interior A ∩ B, h_open, h_subset, And.intro hx_intA hxB⟩)
    exact this

theorem Topology.interior_inter_subset_and_isOpen_of_open {X : Type*}
    [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X} (hB : IsOpen B) :
    ((interior A ∩ B : Set X) ⊆ A ∩ B) ∧ IsOpen (interior A ∩ B) := by
  constructor
  · intro x hx
    exact And.intro (interior_subset hx.1) hx.2
  · exact isOpen_interior.inter hB
